This project requires the following external services
    * Redis (used for handling vote management)
    * ActiveMQ (used for hanlding link fetching)
    * Solr (used for full text search)
    
Example solr config for multicore
    <solr persistent="true" sharedLib="lib">
     <cores adminPath="/admin/cores">
      <core name="irc" instanceDir="irc" />
      <core name="sunspot" instanceDir="sunspot" />
     </cores>
    </solr>
    
    This will go into your solr.home directory, the instanceDir is under solr.home and acts as normal

To setup SunSpot::Rails for multicore, you need to make sure the path attribute is defined, ex
    development:
      solr:
        hostname: localhost
        port: 8080
        path: /solr/sunspot
        log_level: DEBUG

